          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Phase 5: WebSocket Chat — Implementation Plan\n\n## Context\n\nAdding real-time chat with message persistence per stream session. Viewers connect via WebSocket, messages are broadcast to all connected clients and stored in SQLite grouped by stream session.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nBrowser → WS /ws/chat?token=JWT → Hub (1 goroutine)\n                                    ├─ broadcast to all clients\n                                    └─ persist to SQLite (chat_messages)\n\nHub also polls ingest.Manager.IsLive() to auto-create/close stream_sessions.\n```\n\n## New Files\n\n```\ninternal/chat/\n├── hub.go      — central dispatcher: register/unregister/broadcast, session tracking\n├── client.go   — per-connection read/write pumps\n├── store.go    — chat_messages + stream_sessions CRUD\n└── handler.go  — WS upgrade endpoint + chat history API\n```\n\n## Modified Files\n\n- `internal/db/migrations.go` — add `stream_sessions` and `chat_messages` tables\n- `internal/config/config.go` — add `ChatMaxMessageLen`, `ChatRateLimit`\n- `cmd/server/main.go` — wire chat hub + handler\n- `go.mod` — add `nhooyr.io/websocket`\n\n## Schema (add to migrations.go)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS stream_sessions (\n    id         INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    started_at INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT (unixepoch()),\n    ended_at   INTEGER\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS chat_messages (\n    id         INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    session_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES stream_sessions(id),\n    user_id    INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    username   TEXT    NOT NULL,\n    message    TEXT    NOT NULL,\n    created_at INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT (unixepoch())\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chat_messages_session\n    ON chat_messages(session_id, created_at);\n```\n\n## Design Details\n\n### hub.go — Central Hub\n\n```\ntype Hub struct {\n    store      *Store\n    clients    map[*Client]bool\n    register   chan *Client\n    unregister chan *Client\n    broadcast  chan *Message\n    liveCheck  LiveChecker\n    sessionID  int64  // current active session (0 = no stream)\n}\n```\n\n- `Run(ctx)` — main loop: select on register/unregister/broadcast/ctx.Done + ticker every 2s to poll `IsLive()`\n- On `IsLive()` transition `false→true`: insert new `stream_sessions` row, store sessionID\n- On `IsLive()` transition `true→false`: update `ended_at` on current session, reset sessionID\n- On broadcast: write message to all clients, persist to `chat_messages` with current sessionID\n- If no active session (stream offline), still allow chat (sessionID=0, messages not persisted) OR reject messages — **will persist always, create a \"lobby\" session if stream is offline**\n\n### client.go — Per-Connection\n\n```\ntype Client struct {\n    hub      *Hub\n    conn     *websocket.Conn\n    send     chan []byte\n    userID   int64\n    username string\n    role     string\n}\n```\n\n- `readPump()` — reads JSON messages from WS, validates length, rate limits, sends to hub.broadcast\n- `writePump()` — reads from `send` channel, writes JSON to WS, handles ping/pong\n- On disconnect: sends self to hub.unregister\n\n### Message format (JSON over WS)\n\n```json\n// Client → Server\n{\"type\":\"chat\",\"text\":\"hello\"}\n\n// Server → Client\n{\"type\":\"chat\",\"user_id\":1,\"username\":\"alice\",\"text\":\"hello\",\"timestamp\":1710000000}\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"text\":\"alice joined\"}\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"text\":\"Stream started\"}\n```\n\n### handler.go — WebSocket Upgrade + History API\n\n- `GET /ws/chat?token=JWT` — upgrade to WebSocket\n  - Extract token from query param (browser WS API can't set headers)\n  - Validate with `auth.TokenService.Validate()`\n  - Create Client, register with Hub\n- `GET /api/chat/history/{sessionId}` — fetch chat history for a stream session (paginated)\n  - Query `chat_messages` by session_id, ordered by created_at\n  - Optional query params: `?limit=50&before=messageId`\n- `GET /api/chat/sessions` — list stream sessions\n\n### store.go — Data Access\n\n- `CreateSession(ctx) → (sessionID, error)` — INSERT stream_sessions\n- `CloseSession(ctx, sessionID)` — UPDATE ended_at\n- `SaveMessage(ctx, sessionID, userID, username, message) → error`\n- `GetMessages(ctx, sessionID, limit, beforeID) → ([]ChatMessage, error)`\n- `GetSessions(ctx, limit) → ([]StreamSession, error)`\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\nSimple per-client: track last message timestamp, reject if < 500ms apart. Configurable via `CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_MS` env var (default 500).\n\n### Config Additions\n\n```go\nChatMaxMessageLen int  // CHAT_MAX_MSG_LEN, default 500\nChatRateLimitMS   int  // CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_MS, default 500\n```\n\n## Wiring in main.go\n\n```go\n// After auth setup:\nchatStore := chat.NewStore(database)\nchatHub := chat.NewHub(chatStore, ingestMgr)\ngo chatHub.Run(ctx)\n\nchatHandler := chat.NewHandler(chatHub, chatStore, tokenService)\nchatHandler.RegisterRoutes(mux)\n```\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. Add `nhooyr.io/websocket` dependency\n2. Add schema to `internal/db/migrations.go`\n3. Add config fields to `internal/config/config.go`\n4. Create `internal/chat/store.go` — session + message CRUD\n5. Create `internal/chat/hub.go` — dispatcher + session tracking\n6. Create `internal/chat/client.go` — read/write pumps\n7. Create `internal/chat/handler.go` — WS upgrade + history endpoints\n8. Wire into `cmd/server/main.go`\n9. Build and verify\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Start server\ndocker compose up --build\n\n# Register user\nTOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST localhost:8080/api/auth/register \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"alice\",\"password\":\"password123\"}' | jq -r .token)\n\n# Connect to chat via wscat or websocat\nwebsocat \"ws://localhost:8080/ws/chat?token=$TOKEN\"\n# Type: {\"type\":\"chat\",\"text\":\"hello world\"}\n# Should receive broadcast back\n\n# Fetch chat history\ncurl localhost:8080/api/chat/sessions\ncurl localhost:8080/api/chat/history/1?limit=50\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/m.ovchinnikov/.claude/projects/-Users-m-ovchinnikov-GolandProjects-twitch-desent/fbeeed9d-3a9f-42e0-a726-354d9ffc6b34.jsonl",
