          "text": "     1→# Decentralized Twitch (twitch-desent)\n     2→\n     3→## Project Overview\n     4→\n     5→Decentralized streaming platform where **streamers self-host their own servers**. The platform provides either a ready-to-deploy binary (streamer buys domain + VPS, enters data in our installer app like Amnezia, we auto-configure everything) or a managed cloud option (with content moderation — no pirated movies/casinos).\n     6→\n     7→### Key Concept\n     8→Each streamer runs their own Go server (single binary). They can:\n     9→- Add Edge CDN nodes for geo-coverage (e.g., Novosibirsk, St. Petersburg)\n    10→- Host other streamers on their server\n    11→- Register in a Discovery catalog (after moderation) so new viewers can find them\n    12→\n    13→## Architecture\n    14→\n    15→### Video Pipeline\n    16→```\n    17→OBS → RTMP (:1935) → FFmpeg (1080p→720p→480p→360p) → HLS segments (2-4 sec) → HTTP delivery (:443)\n    18→```\n    19→\n    20→### Components (Single Binary)\n    21→- **RTMP Ingest** — accepts OBS stream on port 1935\n    22→- **FFmpeg Transcoder** — multi-quality HLS segmentation\n    23→- **HLS Delivery** — serves `.m3u8` playlists and `.ts` segments via HTTP\n    24→- **WebSocket Chat** — 1 dispatcher goroutine, broadcast to all viewers, rooms per stream\n    25→- **Auth** — JWT-based, middleware on all endpoints\n    26→- **Admin API** — stream settings, CDN node management, user/ban management\n    27→- **SQLite** — local database for users, bans, settings, logs\n    28→\n    29→### External Services (NOT in MVP)\n    30→- **Discovery Service** — cloud catalog of trusted servers (PostgreSQL, moderation)\n    31→- **Edge Nodes** — Go binaries that cache HLS segments from origin server\n    32→\n    33→## Tech Stack\n    34→\n    35→- **Language:** Go 1.23\n    36→- **Database:** SQLite (via `modernc.org/sqlite` — pure Go, no CGO)\n    37→- **HTTP Router:** `net/http` (stdlib, Go 1.22+ routing)\n    38→- **WebSocket:** `nhooyr.io/websocket`\n    39→- **JWT:** `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n    40→- **RTMP:** `github.com/nareix/joy5` or custom RTMP listener\n    41→- **Video:** FFmpeg (external process, managed via `os/exec`)\n    42→- **Config:** Environment variables + YAML config file\n    43→\n    44→## Project Structure\n    45→\n    46→```\n    47→twitch-desent/\n    48→├── cmd/\n    49→│   └── server/\n    50→│       └── main.go              # Entry point, wires everything together\n    51→├── internal/\n    52→│   ├── config/\n    53→│   │   └── config.go            # App configuration (env + yaml)\n    54→│   ├── auth/\n    55→│   │   ├── handler.go           # POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login\n    56→│   │   ├── jwt.go               # JWT generation & validation\n    57→│   │   ├── middleware.go         # Auth middleware (extracts user from token)\n    58→│   │   └── store.go             # User storage (SQLite-backed)\n    59→│   ├── chat/\n    60→│   │   ├── hub.go               # Central dispatcher, room management\n    61→│   │   ├── client.go            # Single WebSocket connection handler\n    62→│   │   └── handler.go           # WS upgrade endpoint\n    63→│   ├── ingest/\n    64→│   │   ├── rtmp.go              # RTMP server, accepts streams\n    65→│   │   └── transcoder.go        # FFmpeg process lifecycle\n    66→│   ├── hls/\n    67→│   │   ├── handler.go           # GET /live/{quality}/playlist.m3u8, GET /live/{quality}/{segment}.ts\n    68→│   │   └── store.go             # Segment file management, cleanup\n    69→│   ├── admin/\n    70→│   │   └── handler.go           # Admin-only API: settings, bans, CDN config\n    71→│   └── db/\n    72→│       ├── sqlite.go            # DB connection, initialization\n    73→│       └── migrations.go        # Schema creation & migrations\n    74→├── CLAUDE.md\n    75→├── TODO.md\n    76→├── go.mod\n    77→└── go.sum\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→## API Endpoints (MVP)\n    81→\n    82→### Auth (no auth required)\n    83→- `POST /api/auth/register` — `{username, password}` → creates user, returns JWT\n    84→- `POST /api/auth/login` — `{username, password}` → validates, returns JWT\n    85→\n    86→### Stream (auth required for some)\n    87→- `GET /live/{quality}/playlist.m3u8` — HLS master/variant playlist (public)\n    88→- `GET /live/{quality}/{segment}.ts` — HLS segment file (public)\n    89→- `GET /api/stream/status` — current stream info (public)\n    90→\n    91→### Chat (auth required)\n    92→- `WS /ws/chat` — WebSocket connection, JWT in query param or first message\n    93→\n    94→### Admin (admin auth required)\n    95→- `GET /api/admin/settings` — get server settings\n    96→- `PUT /api/admin/settings` — update server settings\n    97→- `GET /api/admin/users` — list users\n    98→- `POST /api/admin/ban` — ban a user\n    99→- `DELETE /api/admin/ban/{userId}` — unban\n   100→\n   101→## Development Commands\n   102→\n   103→```bash\n   104→# Run the server\n   105→go run ./cmd/server\n   106→\n   107→# Build single binary\n   108→go build -o desent-server ./cmd/server\n   109→\n   110→# Run tests\n   111→go test ./...\n   112→\n   113→# Run with race detector\n   114→go test -race ./...\n   115→```\n   116→\n   117→## MVP Scope\n   118→\n   119→Building the **streamer server only** (single binary). Mocked auth with login/password (real users in SQLite, but no email verification, no OAuth — just username+password→JWT).\n   120→\n   121→### In Scope\n   122→- RTMP ingest + FFmpeg transcoding to HLS\n   123→- HLS segment serving (multi-quality)\n   124→- WebSocket chat with broadcast\n   125→- Auth: register/login with username+password, JWT tokens\n   126→- Admin API (REST, no UI)\n   127→- SQLite storage\n   128→\n   129→### Out of Scope (future)\n   130→- Discovery service (cloud catalog)\n   131→- Edge CDN nodes\n   132→- Admin React SPA\n   133→- OAuth / social login\n   134→- Installer/deployment scripts\n   135→- Content moderation system\n   136→\n   